git add *  //adds all files to git's tracking (ommit if no files added)
git commit -a -m "<Some Message>" //create a commit with the title <Some Message> (DO NOT USE)
git commit -a //open a vim session to eddit the commit message (see Vim commands below)
git push //self explanitory

git pull //get the latest from github


Vim Commands:

'I' - enter 'I'nsert mode
'G' - 'G'oto end of file
<#>G - 'G'o to line #
'esc' - leave Insert mode or command mode
':wq' - tell vim to 'w'rite and 'q'uit

so: go to end of file, enter Insert mode, write message, enter command mode, write and quit
